results.name: Least number k which can be written as k^2 * j, 0 < j <= k in n ways.
mathematica: t = Sort[ Flatten[ Table[n = k^2*j; If[n < 10^7, n, {}], {k, 10000}, {j, k}]]]; l = Length[t]; t[[Select[ Range[l - 11], t[[ # ]] == t[[ # + 11]] &]]]
results.author: _Leroy Quet_ and _Robert G. Wilson v_, Feb 23 2005
